A Star Point Pattern (43)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f2\froman\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b9\'d9\'c5\'c1;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b White to Play.\b0
\par This is an additional explanation for what we have already studied.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj In <\b Basic Diagram 40\b0 >, black plays dansu at \b\f1 A\lang1033\kerning2\f2\fs20  \lang1042\kerning0\b0\f0\fs18 first and when white plays at \b\f1 B\b0\f0 , black connects with 1.
\par \pard
\par What if black were to play at 1 directly?
\par }
