Diagram 2 (Black, Influence)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par If you wanted to play a diagonal move at 1, it's because you memorized the pattern incorrectly.
\par
\par Please check <\b Basic Diagram 40\b0 > once again.
\par
\par It is a good sacrifice strategy for black to play dansu at 2 and attach with 4.
\par
\par Up to 6, black seals white in perfectly in seonsu and then extends at 8 and has very impressive influence.
\par }
